Job Mission
Assembling, adjusting and qualifying of (sub) modules and/or integrate into a final assembly (scanner system) within the planned production targets.
This job consists 90% of the time assembly activities and support actions on Scanners in system qualification phase (swap parts, test sub assy’s, clean delicate high tech surfaces).
The other 10% are testing activities (leaktesting, High Voltage testing, qualification testing of sub assy’s).

Job Description
- Assembles high quality complex products resulting in  finished products;
- Adjusts the assembled products according to the specifications;
- Testing the product for operation and functioning, with the help of test equipment and test protocols;
- Pointing out and / or solving technical problems during assembly in consultation with the available resources in order to reduce interruption of production;
- Looking for opportunities in reducing process cycle time and takes appropriate action;
- Identifies and acts on quality, Cycle time and safety improving opportunities for ASML benefits.
Education
Intermediate Technical College in Mechanical Engineering (MBO) specialized in precision engineering (e.g. automotive engineering, aviation technology, mechatronics engineering).

Experience
- >3 plus years of experience with high quality precision engineering and familiarity with electronics and / or optics.
Working with computers is a significant part of the job. Making comments on procedures, updating logbooks in Excel. Making disturbance and material notifications in SAP.

Personal skills
- Ability to work in a multi-disciplinary team within a high tech environment;
- Technical drive: curious, persistent, practical, analytical;
- Accurate within the job, the job environment and the work flow;
- Service orientated, good communicator and team worker;
- Flexible. Able to work with changing work packages, plans and colleagues;
- Ability to work with computer systems (MS office, SAP, etc.);
- Stress resistant;
- High Quality and Safety standard;
- Good English vocabulary (read/write).


