Introduction to the job
ASML is seeking a regional Ethics & Compliance Officer to be part of its worldwide Legal team, based in Taiwan, who will drive implementation of the global Ethics & Compliance program within the Asia Region, including establishing, embedding and enforcing elements of the program, with a goal to enhance the compliance mindset and maturity of the regional organization, and ensure that ASML continues to operate with the highest standards of integrity and ethical conduct.  The Regional Ethics & Compliance Officer will partner with the Head of Legal & Compliance Taiwan/Singapore/Malaysia and country management teams to establish and perpetuate a “tone at the top” at the country and regional level that reflects ASML’s commitment to compliance and embed a culture of high performance with integrity at all levels in the organization.

Role and responsibilities
Under the overall leadership of the regional Head of Legal & Compliance Taiwan/Singapore/Malaysia based in Taiwan, and in close coordination with the Global Chief Compliance Officer and Global Chief Ethics Officer based in the Netherlands, enable and drive compliant and ethical business conduct through the effective implementation of the Ethics & Compliance program at the region / country level. 

Working closely with global and local stakeholders, the successful candidate will:
Regionally implement Global Legal Compliance & Ethics programs, including Code of Conduct, Anti-bribery & Corruption, Conflicts of Interest, and Speak Up, driving the establishment and maintenance of local procedures for the relevant policies at the regional and country level, and developing, implementing and coordinating a regional training strategy on these topics;
Stay abreast of the evolving regional regulatory landscape and guidance along with industry leading practices in all relevant areas relevant to the ASML business and operations;
Act as the bridge between the Global Compliance & Ethics Office and regional management on Ethics & Compliance programs and topics, continually providing advice and guidance to the region / country management relevant topics, challenges and major initiatives;
Organize and lead the local Ethics liaison organization with support and content from the Ethics Office;
Together with the Global Ethics Office and/or the Global or Local Legal team, investigate Ethics incidents and claims, including harassment, bullying, fraud, or other violations of the ASML Code of Conduct;
Review and analyze third party due diligence, and implement controls and monitoring for ethical conduct by third parties acting for or on behalf of ASML or other business partners;
Working closely with related functions, build and execute continued controls, monitoring and reporting for various policies and regulations in the defined compliance areas, including anti-bribery & corruption/anti-fraud, gifts & entertainment, and antitrust;
Actively involve region / country leadership to leverage key compliance messages and to maintain high level of awareness (i.e. “tone at the top and at the middle”, implementation at all levels within the organization including in the field).
Work closely with local management, Global RBA,the Global Chief Compliance Officer as well as the Regional Head of Legal and Compliance to drive the agenda and monitor follow up on agreed actions.

Education and experience
At least 10+ years of experience, whether in a legal setting or as an audit or compliance professional;
Previous experience in a foreign headquartered MNC is preferred

Skills
To thrive in this job, you’ll need the following skills:

Strong personal character and commitment to integrity;
Knowledge of and passion for ethical conduct and compliance;
Good business sense;
Ability to influence others and lead;
Proactive, hands-on approach;
Fluent in Mandarin and English


Other information
Occasional International Travel Required

