Logitech is the Sweet Spot for people who want their actions to have a positive global impact while having the flexibility to do it in their own way.

The Team and Role:
As a critical role of the Optical and Sensing Technology(OST) Team, you will contribute significantly to the qualification and development of Optical Sensing System and Opto-Mechanical System in Logitech portfolios from the conceptual product front end, through product development and into successful mass production.

Your Contribution:
Be Yourself. Be Open. Stay Hungry and Humble. Collaborate. Challenge. Decide and just Do. Share our passion for Equality and the Environment. These are the behaviors and values you’ll need for success at Logitech. In this role you will:

• Contribute to the development of new products and technologies, bring innovations and new ideas;
•Aim on optical sensing technology to evaluate new technologies, concepts, configurations or components based on performance, user experience, risk, cost, reliability and manufacturability;
•Specify, design and qualify optical and sensing solutions including Optical Sensing System and Opto-Mechanical System from concept to manufacturing for Logitech products meeting cost, schedule, user experience and sustainability;
•Develop tools and setups to measure or characterize optical and sensing solutions;
•Conduct Design Review, Failure Mode and Effects Analysis(FMEA) Review and Engineering Verification Test(EVT) Review
•Perform measurements & qualification;
•Sustain manufacturing and field quality;
•Collaborate with multi-competence engineering teams in a multi-site environment;
•Collaborate with factories to ensure effective and efficient mass production;

other:
